H0.text: Of those currently independent, which country was the first to give (and not subsequently revoke) full voting rights country-wide to women. Australia

H3.text: Of those currently independent, which country was the first to give (and not subsequently revoke) full voting rights country-wide to women. Nz

A4.text: New Zealand became the first nation in the world in which all women had the right to vote in parliamentary elections.

A5.text: The Electoral Bill granting women the franchise was given Royal Assent by Governor Lord Glasgow on 19 September 1893.
